ENTRY            A0631   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0631001   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 13         35
TITLE      Nonequilibrium effects in alpha-particle-induced
           reactions on gallium isotopes
AUTHOR     (I.A.Rizvi,M.K.Bhardwaj,M.Afzal Ansari,A.K.Chaubey)
REFERENCE  (J,CJP,67,870,1989)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMUA)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC) Variable Energy Cyclotron Center,
           Calcutta.
METHOD     (STTA,GSPEC,BCINT)
           (ACTIV) Beam currents of the order of 100 nA were used.
           The irradiation period was about 45 minutes.
           (EXTB) 60-MeV diffused beam.
ANALYSIS   (DECAY)
DETECTOR   (GELI) High-resolution 100 cm3 Ortec Ge(Li) detector
            (FWHM 2 keV at 1.33 MeV) coupled with a precalibrated
           4096-channel Canberra-88 analyser.
SAMPLE     Natural gallium oxide deposits of thickness 0.9 mg/cm2
           were made on thin aluminium backing of thickness
           6.75 mg/cm2. Energy degrading aluminium foils of
           thickness 20.387 and 6.75 mg/cm2 whenever required,
           to get the desired alpha-particle energy incident
           on each foil.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error. The statistical error
           given in the results is the larger one of the
           internal and external errors (see REL-REF). In
           general these are less than 12%, except for a few
           points. Straggling effects are expected to be
           negligibly small.
REL-REF    (M,,S.F.Mughabghab+,B,NEUT.CS 1A,,89,1981)
ADD-RES    (COMP) Preequilibrium model. Code ALICE/LIVERMORE-82.
HISTORY    (19990604C) By F.C.
           (19990615U) Last checking has been done.
           (19990621A) DATE is corrected
           (20170210A) SD: Institute and Facility codes corrected.
           Data were re-digitized in all Subents. BIB updated.
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              35
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
MEV        PER-CENT
