SUBENT        A0631005   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  5         16
REACTION   (31-GA-69(A,3N)33-AS-70,,SIG)
COMMENT    - By Author - For natural gallium one more reaction
           channel 71Ga(alpha,5n)70As opens at the offset of
           available alpha-particle energy [i.e., at 46.2 MeV],
           whereas the same product nucleus is produced. By
           theoretical calculation we find that the cross
           section for the reaction 71Ga(alpha,5n) is of the
           order of a few millibarns up to 60 MeV, and hence the
           contribution from 69Ga(alpha,3n) is predominant.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Total estimated errors in cross section
           represented by vertical bars. If no bar is depicted,
           the size of the circle includes the magnitude of the
           statistical errors.
